Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Competency hearing on November 21, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

1:42 PM Defendant Jennifer M Carlson in court, in custody.  Attorney Angela Wang in court for Jennifer M Carlson.  Prosecuting attorney Lindsey Hirt in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews case
Atty Wang states her and her client have reviewed the report.  The defendant is objecting to the doctor's finding of not competent but likely to become competent with treatment. Atty Wang requests to schedule a competency hearing. No objection by the State, but they note they were not objecting to the doctor's findings. Court will adjourn for competency hearing before Branch 2. Court notes if the doctor is not available on the date set, Branch 2's clerk will contact parties to set a new date. Neither defense nor the State have any objection to the doctor appearing by video for the next court date..
Competency hearing scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
filed by Dr. Brandon Reintjes, Ph.D.
Review hearing on October 31, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Signed by Judge Jennifer Dorow on September 19, 2022.

2:55 PM Defendant Jennifer M Carlson not in court.  Attorney Angela Wang in court for Jennifer M Carlson. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Abigail Kincheloe.  Defendant is unavailable due to being out of the facility at this time.  DEFENSE COUNSEL REQUESTS ORDER FOR COMPETENCY PURSUANT TO SEC.. 971.14(2).  Court grants request and orders the defendant be examined by the Wisconsin Forensic Unit.  To be done as an outpatient basis within 30 days.  If defendant is returned to the jail, it may be done at the Waukesha County Jail.  Court adjourns for a review hearing and will set this for a review on doctor's report before Branch 7 Reserve due to Judge Dorow being in Trial next month.
Review hearing scheduled for October 31, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

11:02 AM Attorney Angela Wang in court for Jennifer M Carlson. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Abigail Kincheloe. 
Appearance is waived as Def is unavailable due to proceedings in another court of competent jurisdiction.
Hearing scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 02:55 pm.
